<title>UK: Albright &amp; Wilson plant damaged by blast.</title>
<headline>Albright &amp; Wilson plant damaged by blast.</headline>
<dateline>BRISTOL, England 1996-10-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>A plant owned by chemicals company Albright &amp; Wilson in Avonmouth, western England, was hit by a severe explosion on Thursday which injured five people, a spokesman for the Bristol fire service said.</p>
<p>He said there was a severe fire after the explosion, with a very large smoke plume but the fire was now under control. The injuries were minor and mainly due to smoke inhalation.</p>
<p>He could not say how toxic the smoke plume was but local people had been advised to stay indoors and close windows.</p>
